                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="14126255" author="acoliver" created="Tue, 9 Sep 2014 00:01:13 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;this patches trunk, I can supply against other branches if desired.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14126270" author="acoliver" created="Tue, 9 Sep 2014 00:10:03 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;(cleaned out stuff from earlier patch sorry about that)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14126452" author="daijy" created="Tue, 9 Sep 2014 02:38:43 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Do you mind adding a unit test?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14126830" author="acoliver" created="Tue, 9 Sep 2014 11:24:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure, any suggestions on how to go about that? Meaning there aren&apos;t currently any unit tests under &quot;test&quot; that actually use hdfs:// &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I could easily create a pig script that loaded one jar and either resolved it locally or didn&apos;t...provided I figure out the hdfs:// part.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14127264" author="daijy" created="Tue, 9 Sep 2014 18:26:52 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Take a look of TestPigRunner.scriptsInDfsTest, it uploads a Pig script to dfs and run the remote script. Also TestGrunt.validate, which invoke Main directly in test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14131756" author="acoliver" created="Fri, 12 Sep 2014 18:08:48 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks! where do you want it? Its own Test file or some particular one?  TestMain seemed the most obvious to me....&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14134209" author="acoliver" created="Mon, 15 Sep 2014 19:00:06 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Unit test for -j&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14147126" author="daijy" created="Thu, 25 Sep 2014 01:00:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thinking that again, I feel we might need to deal with mixed jar origin in one job, eg, some jars are in hdfs and some jars are local. We shall allow the full scheme so user can specify if the jar is local or hdfs. However, pig.additional.jars is colon separated and make it impossible. I&apos;d like to introduce a comma separated equivalent to make the things flow. Attach patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14147128" author="daijy" created="Thu, 25 Sep 2014 01:01:58 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;hcat/hive jars are known to be locally, so bin/pig will pass &lt;a href=&quot;file://xxx&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;file://xxx&lt;/a&gt; to Pig to clarify.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14172451" author="acoliver" created="Wed, 15 Oct 2014 16:06:52 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;will do.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14172452" author="acoliver" created="Wed, 15 Oct 2014 16:07:40 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;oh you beat me to it, even better &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14190713" author="thejas" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 19:58:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Daniel, can you also include the doc edits ? &lt;br/&gt;
Also the commented line &quot;#HADOOP_OPTS&quot; can be deleted.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14190774" author="daijy" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 20:29:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed the doc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14190819" author="thejas" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 20:53:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think it would be useful to retain mention of the old additional.jars parameter in the web docs, Saying that it is similar to .jars.comma but separated by the OS path charactor and does not allow for scheme to be specified (and that the use of jars.comma is preferred)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14190821" author="thejas" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 20:54:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think we should also change the jira title and description to indicate what is being implemented.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14190831" author="daijy" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 21:00:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Put a note of preference &quot;pig.additional.jars.comma&quot; over &quot;pig.additional.jars&quot; in the doc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14190848" author="thejas" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 21:09:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14190860" author="daijy" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 21:16:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch committed to trunk and 0.14 branch. Thanks Thejas for review!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14190877" author="daijy" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 21:24:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=acoliver&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;acoliver&quot;&gt;Andrew C. Oliver&lt;/a&gt; for discovering the issue and share the initial fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14191348" author="rohini" created="Fri, 31 Oct 2014 04:46:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=daijy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;daijy&quot;&gt;Daniel Dai&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;br/&gt;
    pig.additional.jars.comma - naming sounds weird. Would it be possible to just support both : and , in pig.additional.jars itself and mention in documentation to use , as separator if path has URIs. Can split on , if present in the path else fall back to spliting on : &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14191466" author="daijy" created="Fri, 31 Oct 2014 06:31:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agree pig.additional.jars.comma is a weird name. How about &quot;pig.additional.jars.uris&quot;? I prefer a simple logic to parse the string, otherwise it is hard to explain to the user and might cause unexpected result.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14191469" author="rohini" created="Fri, 31 Oct 2014 06:33:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;pig.additional.jars.uris sounds good. +1 for that change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14191481" author="daijy" created="Fri, 31 Oct 2014 06:43:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attach patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14191484" author="daijy" created="Fri, 31 Oct 2014 06:44:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-4160&quot; title=&quot;Provide a way to pass local jars in pig.additional.jars when using a remote url for a script&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-4160&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-4160&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;-changepropertyname.patch committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
